From December 1, the law came into force, according to which every migrant will be obliged to pass the exam for knowledge of the Russian language.
So far, this rule applies only to those who intend to work in the field of service, housing and communal services, household and retail trade.
However, over time, - the FMS promise - tests will become mandatory for all visitors.
At the same time, it will be necessary to pass not only the language, but also Russian history, and the foundations of legislation.
Knowledge of the language will have to be confirmed both for obtaining and for renewing a work permit.
The exception applies only to citizens of those countries where Russian is the state language.
People who managed to obtain certificates and diplomas of education before the collapse of the USSR in 1991 are not subject to the law.
