He loves people with good upbringing and high titles, and they love him.
One of the galleries of Somerset House has been turned into a glamorous podium of sixty meters in length, which offers a change of roles: the visitor takes the place of models and must parade along the podium, contemplating the "spectators" of dreams that sparkle with Valentino's masterpieces, such as the dress that Jacqueline Kennedy chose for her wedding dress.
