Other people may have children.
“But it’s important for me to have my own money and time,” says another 20-year-old.
Men and women cite their careers, stress, and housing and education prices as reasons that prevent them from having children.
So, no matter how much the government tries to encourage its citizens to have children, as far as childbearing is concerned, Singaporeans have the final say.
