Also during the summit, the bloc’s defence ministers met in advance to approve the 2013 Action Plan, which aims to strengthen dialogue and unanimity on the protection of the region.
Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Brazil, Uruguay, Chile, Guyana, Suriname and Paraguay form UNASUR, although the latter has been suspended.
Peru holds the presidency of the regional bloc.
